<p>Lithuania temporarily shut air traffic at Vilnius airport overnight after dozens of helium balloons carrying smuggled cigarettes entered its airspace late on Tuesday, forcing flight diversions and stranding thousands of passengers; the airport reopened early Wednesday morning [politico.eu#1][theguardian.com#1][euronews.com#1]. Prime Minister Inga Ruginienė called an urgent National Security Committee meeting and publicly urged Belarus to take responsibility for the incidents, saying Lithuania needs concrete solutions [politico.eu#1]. Authorities said the operation appeared coordinated, border guards intercepted multiple balloons and several suspects were detained as an investigation continues [politico.eu#1][dw.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/rgMpqW9zHrW03dmsh57dNeuSaFLYW7sVPtSR2wL6c-olXQbngnGue594fiXKGrA7vxeHk1w6SkEytb75j6gaIP78fDivLuhG7T8JFuX3-ijy5T66NyEVnOJnmfehHMplfGVMpEUhYcf8W4h714kS9l5R3ms6ESWyLTNp1rkPepRGrNmc' alt='Vilnius airport after temporary suspension of flights amid balloon smuggling incident' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Coordinated tactic: Lithuania&#x27;s National Crisis Management Center described the launches as a coordinated operation rather than a single-point release, prompting an investigation into who ordered it [politico.eu#1].</li><li>Border measures: After the balloon incursion, Lithuania temporarily suspended some border crossings with Belarus as part of immediate security measures [dw.com#1].</li><li>Smuggling motive: Reports say smugglers use airborne deliveries because Belarusian cigarettes are cheaper and attract demand inside the EU market [theguardian.com#1][euronews.com#1].</li><li>Scale uncertainty: Border Guard officials confirmed 12 balloons were intercepted but said the total number could be much higher, citing initial estimates up to about 200 objects observed [politico.eu#1].</li></ul><blockquote>I would very much like Belarus to take responsibility for these incidents - Prime Minister Inga Ruginienė</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Prime Minister Inga Ruginienė: She demanded concrete solutions, convened the National Security Committee and said she wants Belarus to take responsibility for the incidents [politico.eu#1]. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/lithuania-closes-main-airport-after-overnight-balloon-barrage/'>politico.eu</a>)</li><li>Border Guard Commander Rustamas Liubajevas: He reported &#x27;several dozen&#x27; balloons detected, 12 intercepted, and said the number of detained suspects could change as intelligence operations continue [politico.eu#1]. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/lithuania-closes-main-airport-after-overnight-balloon-barrage/'>politico.eu</a>)</li><li>Vilnius airport spokesperson: The airport said roughly 30 flights were diverted or canceled and about 4,000 passengers were affected during the temporary suspension [politico.eu#1][euronews.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/lithuania-closes-main-airport-after-overnight-balloon-barrage/'>politico.eu</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/lithuania-closes-main-airport-after-overnight-balloon-barrage/'>Helium balloons carrying smuggled cigarettes shut down Lithuania’s main airport</a> - politico.eu</li><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/2025/10/22/vilnius-airport-closed-after-cigarette-smuggling-balloons-spotted'>Vilnius airport closed after cigarette-smuggling balloons spotted</a> - euronews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/smugglers-balloons-force-shutdown-of-vilnius-airport'>Smugglers’ balloons force shutdown of Vilnius airport</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/lithuania-s-main-airport-shut-after-balloon-sightings/a-74449401'>Lithuania&#x27;s main airport shut after balloon sightings</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/lithuania-suspends-air-traffic-at-capital-airport-over-smugglers-balloons-from-belarus-ws-e-13943959.htm